title: additionalProperties inconsistency across built-in tool schemas
---
cx-reviewer audit (2026-05-21): some built-in tools set ('additionalProperties', Bool false) at the schema root, others don't. Inconsistent strictness across:
- send_message at src/tools_builtin.ml:56 — no additionalProperties
- file_read at src/tools_builtin_io.ml:172 — no additionalProperties
- shell_exec at src/tools_builtin_util.ml:1313 — no additionalProperties
- bg_shell_status at src/tools_bg_shell.ml:22 — no additionalProperties
- vs background_task_tools.ml:116 which does set it

Impact: lenient providers ignore the difference; strict providers (some Anthropic/MiniMax responses, Gemini) may behave differently for tools with/without it. Best practice: set additionalProperties:false consistently to reject hallucinated extra args.

Fix: audit every tool schema; set ('additionalProperties', Bool false) on every top-level object schema. Add a regression test in test_tools.ml that fails if any registered tool's schema omits additionalProperties.

Tag: tools, schema, anthropic-api, openai-api